Maharashtra
Sep 21, 2014
Rape
Description:
			A case was booked against a middle-aged man for allegedly raping a woman on several occasions.

Thane police has filed a case against a Kalyan-based builder Madhukar Mhatre (50) last night based on the complaint of victim, whose husband worked as an site supervisor at the builder's firm, assistant police inspector at Dombivili police station H D Redekar said.

According to the complainant, she was allegedly raped by Mhatre in December 2013 when she was at his house with her two children and he also threatened her to sack her husband from the job if she resists.

Later, on three different occasions, the woman alleged that she was raped by the builder in July and August this year.

